Peg hath kat ki kotsi, aanky maanay bhunsii kali mashii;
Kaan naak faadi baandhyaa keesh, vaalii baandiya angaliyo vish.

(Note: I've translated the couplet as it is, without adding any extra words)

Here is the translation:

Above is the hollow of the stomach, the sound of Ohkār in my mouth; 
Finger and hair are entangled, something from this is the matter of some person.

It sees fear at once, it sees darkness; 
it runs in the black night, it's bound; 
it gives foot in water, fearing; 
it jumps out of the sea naturally.
